From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Fujisan Developer <fujisan@atari>
Date: Tue, 17 Mar 2026 00:00:00 -0800
Subject: [PATCH] Fix uint8_t truncation of write_size in NETSIO_SYNC_RESPONSE

The OPEN DIRECTORY command passes a 256-byte payload to FujiNet, causing
NetSIO::setWriteSize(256) to encode sync_write_size = 257 (data + checksum)
as a little-endian uint16_t in the SYNC_RESPONSE packet bytes [4:5].

On the emulator side, write_size was declared as uint8_t, so 257 (0x0101)
was truncated to 1. The SIO write frame handler then collected only 1 byte
(the first byte of the directory path, e.g. '/' = 0x2F) and sent it as
the checksum byte, leaving FujiNet waiting for 255 more data bytes that
never arrived. FujiNet computed checksum 0x2F from the one received byte
and compared it against the 0x00 it eventually got, producing the repeated
"Data Frame Chksum error, calc 2f, rcv 00" log lines.

Any command whose payload >= 255 bytes hits this bug. OPEN DIRECTORY is
the canonical case at exactly 256 bytes.

Fix: declare write_size as uint16_t, matching the protocol encoding.
---
 src/netsio.c | 3 ++-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/netsio.c b/src/netsio.c
index 3fafc31d..1e4340d3 100644
--- a/src/netsio.c
+++ b/src/netsio.c
@@ -648,7 +648,8 @@ static void *fujinet_rx_thread(void *arg) {
             case NETSIO_SYNC_RESPONSE:
             {
                 /* packet: [cmd][sync#][ack_type][ack_byte][write_lo][write_hi] */
-                uint8_t resp_sync, ack_type, ack_byte, write_size;
+                uint8_t resp_sync, ack_type, ack_byte;
+                uint16_t write_size;
 
                 if (n < 6)
                 {
